<document>
	<title>The management of portal hypertension in cystic fibrosis.</title>

	<author>Schuster-S-R.</author>
	<author>Shwachman-H.</author>
	<author>Toyama-W-M.</author>
	<author>Rubino-A.</author>
	<author>Taik-Khaw-K.</author>

	<source>J-Pediatr-Surg. 1977 Apr. 12(2). P 201-6.</source>

	<abstract>We have found that with proper selection and preoperative
   preparation, a major portosystemic shunt can be done with
   considerable safety in a majority of cystic fibrosis patients and
   thus provide them with significant palliation and improved quality of
   life.</abstract>

